Hurricane Irma Georgia Travel Information
Sept. 9, 2017 - Zone B and C in Chatham County will be moving to a voluntary evacuation order. The mandatory evacuation order issued by Gov. Deal remains in effect for all of Zone A throughout the coastal region. The Georgia Department of Transportation has removed contraflow operations on Interstate 16, returning normal traffic configurations for both east and westbound travel lanes. This allows the state to transition our contraflow resources westward.